### Adding a skill without Python (pipeline v1)
```yaml
# vault/.system/skill-definitions/my_skill.yaml
name: my_skill
graph: pipeline
system_prompt: |
  You are ...
nodes:
  - plan
  - draft
  - critic          # optional
  - human_approval  # optional — enables interrupt gate
  - finalize
node_prompts:        # optional — defaults generated from step id
  plan: "Plan the work for: {user_input}"
max_cost_per_run: 0.20
```

## Gemini free tier
- Flash: ~5 RPM, **20 RPD** — daily limit is the real blocker
- Autonomous runs defer via IVT when only interactive reserve remains
- Do not health-probe Gemini every poll; embedding cache avoids re-embed on restart

## API quick reference
- `GET /api/v1/skills/interrupts` — pending IVT rows (budget, degraded, HITL)
- `GET /api/v1/skills/pending` — enriched HITL approvals
- `GET /api/v1/health` — includes budget snapshot + degraded flag

